revision.text:
{{Infobox games | name = VI Bolivarian Games | logo = | size = | caption = | host city = [[Maracaibo]] | country = {{Flagcountry|VEN}} | motto = | nations participating = 6 | teams participating = | athletes participating = 1122 | events = 17 sports | opening ceremony = {{Start date|1970|08|22}} | closing ceremony = {{End date|1970|09|06}} | officially opened by = [[Rafael Caldera]] | athlete's oath = [[Brígido Iriarte]] | judge's oath = | torch lighter = [[José Encarnación Romero|José "Pachencho" Romero]] | stadium = [[Estadio José Pachencho Romero|Estadio Olímpico del Complejo Polideportivo]] | length = | indprize = | tmprize = | website = | previous = [[1965 Bolivarian Games|1965 Quito and Guayaquil]] | next = [[1973 Bolivarian Games|1973 Panama City]] }} The '''VI [[Bolivarian Games]]''' (Spanish: ''Juegos Bolivarianos'') were a [[multi-sport event]] held between August 22 - September 6, 1970, at the [[Estadio José Pachencho Romero|Estadio Olímpico del Complejo Polideportivo]]<ref name=eltiempo_01> {{ Citation | last = | first = | date = August 23, 1970 | title = Brillante fue la inauguración de los VI Juegos Bolivarianos | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=N2osnxbUuuUC&dat=19700823&printsec=frontpage&hl=en | page = 10 (original page no.: 18) | newspaper = [[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]] | language = Spanish | accessdate = January 14, 2013 }} </ref> in [[Maracaibo]], [[Venezuela]]. The Games were organized by the Bolivarian Sports Organization ([[ODEBO]]).
The Games were officially opened by Venezuelan president [[Rafael Caldera]]. Torch lighter was javelin thrower [[José Encarnación Romero|José "Pachencho" Romero]], who won the first gold medal ever in athletics for Venezuela at the [[Athletics at the 1947-48 Bolivarian Games|1947–48 Bolivarian Games]]. The olympic stadium in Maracaibo was later named after him. The athlete's oath was sworn by athlete [[Brígido Iriarte]], who the gold medal in pentathlon at the [[Athletics at the 1951 Bolivarian Games|1951 Bolivarian Games]].<ref name=bolivia/>
A detailed history of the early editions of the Bolivarian Games between 1938 and 1989 was published in a book written (in Spanish) by José Gamarra Zorrilla, former president of the [[Bolivian Olympic Committee]], and first president (1976-1982) of [[ODESUR]].<ref name=bolivia> {{ Citation | last = Gamarra Zorrilla | first = José | date = | title = Bolivia Olímpica Capítulos VI al VIII | url = http://www.andesacd.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Bolivia-Ol%C3%ADmpica-Cap%C3%ADtulos-VI-al-VIII.pdf | publisher = ANDES Academia del Conocimiento y el Desarrollo "Fernando Diez de Medina" | language = Spanish | accessdate = October 22, 2012 }} </ref> Gold medal winners from Ecuador were published by the [[Ecuadorian National Olympic Committee|Comité Olímpico Ecuatoriano]].<ref name=coe> {{ Citation |last= |first= |date= |title=CUADRO DE MEDALLISTAS ECUATORIANOS EN LA HISTORIA DE LOS J. D. B. POR EDICIÓN |url=http://www.coe.org.ec/pdf/Medallas_Ecuador/JUEGOS_BOLIVARIANOS_1938-1997.pdf |publisher=Comité Olímpico Ecuatoriano |language=Spanish |accessdate=October 22, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120608185327/http://www.coe.org.ec/pdf/Medallas_Ecuador/JUEGOS_BOLIVARIANOS_1938-1997.pdf |archivedate=June 8, 2012 |df= }} </ref>
== Participation == About 1122 Athletes from 6 countries were reported to participate:<ref name=bolivia/><ref name=eltiempo_02> {{ Citation | last = Beals | first = Herman | date = September 6, 1970 | title = Venezuela se quedó con máximo título | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=N2osnxbUuuUC&dat=19700906&printsec=frontpage&hl=en | page = 35 (original page no.: 21) | newspaper = [[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]] | language = Spanish | accessdate = January 14, 2013 }} </ref> {{col-begin}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Bolivia}} *{{flag|Colombia}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Ecuador}} *{{flag|Panama}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Peru}} *{{flag|Venezuela}} {{col-end}}
== Sports == The following 17 sports were explicitly mentioned:<ref name=bolivia/><ref name=coe/> For the first time, softball was included. On the other hand, initially scheduled events in sailing, chess, and table tennis were cancelled.<ref name=eltiempo_02/> {{col-begin|width=100%}} {{col-1-of-3}} *[[Aquatic sports]] **[[File:Diving pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Diving (sport)|Diving]] ({{detailslink|Swimming at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) **[[File:Swimming pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Swimming (sport)|Swimming]] ({{detailslink|Swimming at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Athletics pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] ({{detailslink|Athletics at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Baseball pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Baseball]] ({{detailslink|Baseball at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Basketball pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Basketball]] ({{detailslink|Basketball at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Boxing pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Boxing]] ({{detailslink|Boxing at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) {{col-2-of-3}} *[[Cycling]] **[[File:Cycling (road) pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Road Cycling]] ({{detailslink|Cycling at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) **[[File:Cycling (track) pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Track Cycling]] ({{detailslink|Cycling at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Equestrian pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Equestrianism|Equestrian]] ({{detailslink|Equestrian at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Fencing pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Fencing]] ({{detailslink|Fencing at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Football pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Association football|Football]] ({{detailslink|Football at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Gymnastics (artistic) pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Artistic gymnastics|Gymnastics (artistic)]] ({{detailslink|Gymnastics at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) {{col-3-of-3}} *[[File:Judo pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Judo]] ({{detailslink|Judo at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Softball pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Softball]] ({{detailslink|Softball at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Shooting pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Shooting sport|Shooting]] ({{detailslink|Shooting at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Tennis pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Tennis]] ({{detailslink|Tennis at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Volleyball (indoor) pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Volleyball]] ({{detailslink|Volleyball at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Weightlifting pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] ({{detailslink|Weightlifting at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) *[[File:Wrestling pictogram.svg|30px]] [[Wrestling]] ({{detailslink|Wrestling at the 1970 Bolivarian Games}}) {{col-end}}
