{{Infobox football biography | name = Billy Mataitai | image = | fullname = Billy Mataitai | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|07|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tahiti]] | height = | position = [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[AS Manu-Ura]] | clubnumber = 20 | youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2003– |clubs1 = [[AS Manu-Ura]] |caps1 = |goals1 = | pcupdate = 13 January 2012 | nationalyears1 = 2004–2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] | nationalcaps1 = 16 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | ntupdate = 13 January 2012 }}
'''Billy Mataitai''' (born 20 July 1983) in [[Tahiti]] is a [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder (football)|Midfielder]]. He currently plays for [[AS Manu-Ura]]<ref>http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/billy-mataitai/</ref> in the [[Tahiti Division Fédérale]] and the [[Tahiti national football team]].<ref>{{NFT player|pid=7585}}</ref>
