A '''cutback''' is a sudden change in direction by a ball carrier in [[American football]], usually against the flow of the play.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportsdefinitions.com/american-football/Cutback.html|title=What is Cutback in American Football? Definition and Meaning|publisher=}}</ref> One common type of cutback would be turning an [[end run]] into a run down the middle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dictionary.com/browse/cutback|title=the definition of cutback|publisher=}}</ref> It is a common type of [[Juke (football move)|juke]] and the basis of the [[counter run]].
