{{Dutch Basketball League awards}} The '''[[Dutch Basketball League]] Most Valuable Player Award''' is an annual award given to the [[most valuable player]] in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] highest professional [[basketball]] league. The award is given after the regular season and was first handed out in 1974. Six Dutch players have won the award so far, with [[Arvin Slagter]] being the last in 2014. [[Kees Akerboom, Sr.]] (1980, 1981, 1985) and [[Leon Rodgers]] (2005–2007) are the all-time leaders in Dutch MVP awards.
