{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Myyrmäen jalkapallostadion | coordinates = {{coord|60|15.726|N|24|50.291|E|type:landmark_region:FI-ES|display=inline,title}} | former_names = ISS Stadion, Pohjola Stadion | image = [[Image:Pohjola stadion.jpg|300px]] | location = [[Vantaa]], [[Finland]] | nickname = | built = 2000 | opened = 2000 | seating_capacity = 4.700 | tenants = [[Allianssi Vantaa]], [[Pallokerho-35]] (PK-35 Vantaa<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.iltalehti.fi/jalkapallo/200812178791418_jp.shtml|title= PK-35 vaihtaa Vantaalle|accessdate=30 December 2008 |work= |publisher= Iltalehti|date=17 December 2008}}</ref>) | dimensions = 105 m x 68 m | }} '''Myyrmäen jalkapallostadion''',<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pk35vantaa.fi/seura/stadion/ |title= MYYRMÄEN JALKAPALLOSTADION|accessdate=4 April 2016 |work= |publisher= Pk-35 Vantaa|date=}}</ref> formerly '''ISS Stadion'''<ref>{{Cite web|url= http://www.energia-areena.fi/uutiset.html?89|title= Jalkapallostadionista ISS Stadion - PK-35:n edustusjoukkueet Vantaalle|accessdate= 30 December 2008|work= |publisher= Energia-Areena|date= 17 December 2008|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090211121450/http://energia-areena.fi/uutiset.html?89|archivedate= 11 February 2009|df= }}</ref> and '''Pohjola Stadion'''<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.vantaansanomat.fi/Urheilu/Urheilu-Uutiset/Myyrmaen-stadionille-haetaan-uutta-kumppania|title= Myyrmäen stadionille haetaan uutta kumppania |accessdate=30 December 2008 |work= |publisher= Vantaan Sanomat|date=22 July 2008}}</ref> is a [[football (soccer)|football]] [[stadium]] in [[Vantaa]], [[Finland]]. It is the homeground of [[Pallokerho-35|PK-35 Vantaa]], which plays in [[Kolmonen]]. The stadium holds 4,700 and was built in 2000.
The [[IFAF]] [[2018 European Championship of American football|2018 European Championship]] of [[American Football]] will be held in Myyrmäen jalkapallostadion at 29 July - 4 August 2018.
==Specs== *Pitch: Artificial turf *Pitch dimensions: 105*68 *Floodlights: 1,500 lux
