{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Pakistan Karate Federation |abbrev = PKF |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Karate]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|1988}} |aff = [[World Karate Federation]] |affdate = |region = [[Asian Karatedo Federation]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Lahore]] |location = Olympic House |president = Muhammad Jehangir<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.sports.gov.pk/About%20Us/telephonedirectory.htm Pakistan Sports Board<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> |secretary = Shamim Hashmi (late)<ref name=autogenerated1 /> |url = |countryflag = Pakistan |more = }} The '''Pakistan Karate Federation''' is the national [[Sports governing body|governing body]] to develop and promote the sport of [[Karate]] in the [[Pakistan]].
